### TimeGate API examples (VS Code REST Client / similar)
### Dev: bun install && bun run prisma:migrate && bun run prisma:seed && bun run start:dev
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = <paste_jwt_here>

### Login (public)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@timegate.local",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!"
}

### Create user (ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "ops@timegate.local",
  "password": "ChangeMe123!",
  "role": "MANAGER"
}

### List sites
GET {{baseUrl}}/sites?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create site (ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sites
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "East Campus",
  "address": "55 River Rd",
  "timezone": "America/Chicago"
}

### List employees (filters: siteId, employeeId, from, to, search, isActive)
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees?siteId=&search=ada&page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create employee (ADMIN)
POST {{baseUrl}}/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "department": "QA",
  "position": "Engineer",
  "siteId": "<site_uuid>",
  "faceEmbedding": [0.01, 0.02, 0.03]
}

### List devices (filters: siteId, status, from, to)
GET {{baseUrl}}/devices?siteId=<site_uuid>&status=ONLINE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Device heartbeat (ADMIN + MANAGER)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/devices/<device_uuid>/heartbeat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ONLINE"
}

### Record check-in (ADMIN + MANAGER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/attendance
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employeeId": "<employee_uuid>",
  "deviceId": "<device_uuid>",
  "type": "CHECK_IN",
  "confidence": 0.94
}

### List attendance (filters: siteId via device, employeeId, from, to)
GET {{baseUrl}}/attendance?siteId=<site_uuid>&employeeId=<employee_uuid>&from=2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z&to=2026-12-31T23:59:59.999Z&page=1&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Recognition log (ADMIN + MANAGER)
POST {{baseUrl}}/logs
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "<device_uuid>",
  "employeeId": "<employee_uuid>",
  "success": true,
  "confidence": 0.91,
  "imageUrl": "https://storage.example.com/captures/2026/01/abc.jpg"
}

### List logs (filters: siteId, employeeId, from, to)
GET {{baseUrl}}/logs?siteId=<site_uuid>&from=2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Luxand (set LUXAND_API_TOKEN in .env). Multipart: field employeeId + file field photo.
### Enroll — create Luxand person, save luxandPersonUuid on employee (ADMIN)
# curl -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" -F "employeeId=EMPLOYEE_UUID" -F "photo=@./face.jpg" {{baseUrl}}/luxand/enroll

### Add face — extra photo for existing Luxand person (ADMIN)
# curl -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" -F "employeeId=EMPLOYEE_UUID" -F "photo=@./face2.jpg" {{baseUrl}}/luxand/add-face

### Verify — Luxand photo/verify + RecognitionLog (ADMIN + MANAGER)
# curl -H "Authorization: Bearer TOKEN" -F "employeeId=EMPLOYEE_UUID" -F "deviceId=DEVICE_UUID" -F "photo=@./capture.jpg" {{baseUrl}}/luxand/verify

### Mobile provisioning (ADMIN + MANAGER) => returns lifetime_token for kiosk app
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/mobile/provision
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "siteId": "<site_uuid>",
  "deviceName": "Kiosk Front Desk",
  "location": "Hall principal"
}

### Mobile verify (public endpoint, uses lifetime_token from provisioning)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/mobile/verify
Authorization: Bearer <lifetime_token>
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

# Form fields:
# - photo: <image file>
